Generate a Postgres SQL Query based on below rule

Case 1: If user asks for aggregation and do not mention top/Bottom/Highest/Lowest:
   - average → use AVG(index_value)
   - total or sum → use SUM(index_value)
   - Any Other aggregation if user ask, always do calculation on index_value column
Then SQL Query Structure is: 
select year, indicator, $relevant_columns,aggregate_function(index_value) from data_view
WHERE conditions are: indicator LIKE'$indicator', $where_conditions
group by year, indicator, $relevant_columns
order by year, indicator, $relevant_columns

Case 2: If user asks for aggregation and also  mention top/Bottom/Highest/Lowest: Then
   - average → use AVG(inidicator_value)
   - total or sum → use SUM(index_value)
   - For any Other aggregation if user ask, always do calculation on index_value column
Then SQL Query Structure is: 
select year, indicator, $relevant_columns,aggregate_function(index_value) from data_view
WHERE conditions are: indicator LIKE'$indicator', $where_conditions
group by year, indicator, $relevant_columns
order by index_value

